      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PLAYA BLANCA (9) registered another strong performance last start when she battled on well to be beaten just over 2m at Menangle, adding to a string of placings. Hard to know where she gets to from this awkward draw but she has a decent record at this circuit and distance so with even luck could break through. MAGNETIC STORM (1) overcame a wide barrier to score easily in the city two starts back before placing here last time. Up in grade but gets the aid of the ace draw. WITHDISTINCTION (5) has been freshened since breaking in the Junee Cup last time but was kept up to the mark with a trial and had some decent form prior including a Menangle second from a wider barrier three back. TIGER PRINCE (2) was drawn on the back row last time so is much better served by this barrier and won the previous time he raced here.",
